, Angel, Berto, Cristobal, Dinora, Eloisa, Francisco, Generoso, Gustavo, Juan.","English: variant of <b>Donne</b>, itself a variant of   Dunn  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dunn","meanings":["Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Duinn</b>, <b>Ó Doinn</b> ‘descendant of <i>Donn</i>’, a byname meaning ‘brown-haired’ or ‘chieftain’. Compare   Dunne  . This name has sometimes been Anglicized as   Brown  .","English: nickname for a dark complexioned or swarthy man, from Middle English <i>dun</i> ‘dun, dark’ (Old English <i>dunn</i> ‘dull brown’).","Scottish: habitational name from Dun in Angus, named with Gaelic <i>dùn</i> ‘fort’. Compare   Dun  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"no one was born as the daughter of Einudd ab Aelan and Queen Einudd Ap Aelan. She married no one about 1069. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1071, in Wales, United Kingdom."},"et":{"–1071":"–1071","1031–1073":"1031–1073","1031–1074":"1031–1074","1047–Male":"1047–Surnud","1060–1126":"1060–1126","1030–1070":"1030–1070","1010–1030":"1010–1030","1126":"1126","Abt 1047":"umbes 1047","Abt 1069":"umbes 1069","1047":"1047","1010":"1010","1031":"1031","1030":"1030","1074":"1074","1073":"1073","1071":"1071","1060":"1060","1070":"1070","Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Wales, United Kingdom","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"–1071":"–1071","1031–1073":"1031–1073","1031–1074":"1031–1074","1047–Male":"1047–Kuollut","1060–1126":"1060–1126","1030–1070":"1030–1070","1010–1030":"1010–1030","1126":"1126","Abt 1047":"noin 1047","Abt 1069":"noin 1069","1047":"1047","1010":"1010","1031":"1031","1030":"1030","1074":"1074","1073":"1073","1071":"1071","1060":"1060","1070":"1070","Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales","Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Picardie, Ranska"},"fr":{"–1071":"–1071","1031–1073":"1